==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cafeteria
<hw>Caf`e*te"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>cafeti⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A restaurant or
caf⟦eacute⟧ at which the patrons serve themselves with food kept at a
counter, typically paying a cashier at the end of the counter and taking
the food to tables to eat.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a room within a building functioning in the same
manner as a cafeteria{1}. In certain organizations, as schools, the food
may be provided gratis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cafetorium</ent>⟦br⟧
